#ad Holiday cookies + @californiaclingpeaches make the perfect winter dessert! From kids to adults, who doesn't love cookies at every Christmas party? These treats are easy to make and will delight your friends and family. #CaliforniaClingPeaches are found at your local grocery store, or might even be in your pantry right now, so they are always convenient to feature in any holiday dish, including these cookies. Here's how to make them.

Use the jam recipe from californiaclingpeaches.com or follow the directions below. 
Ingredients: 4 (15 oz) cans California Cling Peaches, strained, ⅓ cup sugar, ¼ cup corn starch, pinch of salt.

California Cling Peach Jam Directions:
1. In a medium saucepan place all jam ingredients and simmer while mashing with a potato masher until all corn starch is dissolved. Cook 3 minutes while whisking. Remove from heat and cool.
2. Fill jam jars, making sure the jam is cooled completely before sealing with a tight-fitting lid. Store jam in the refrigerator.

Holiday Cookie Directions: 
Make your favorite sugar cookie recipe or get premade sugar cookie dough. Roll out dough and cut shapes using holiday cookie cutters. You will need two of the exact same shapes, to stack on top of each other, for each of the finished cookies. Cut a circle out of the middle of one of each of the shapes of cookies. Bake according to package directions. 

Let cookies cool. Spread California Cling Peach Jam on one cookie. Sprinkle powdered sugar on the cookie with the hole. Place the powdered sugar topped cookie on top of the jam covered cookie. Serve at your next holiday party!

#ad What food instantly makes you think of your childhood? As a child of the ‘80s and ‘90s there were many for me but hot sandwiches stuffed in a pocket shape were always a fun meal choice! I thought it would be fun to take the childhood nostalgia and up the taste by making these at home with better ingredients. So I created my Cheesy @minutericeus Jalapeño Rice and Chicken Pockets. 
 
Directions:
This recipe starts with my favorite flavor rice of the moment, Minute Rice Jalapeño Rice Cups. Heat one cup up in the microwave for 60 seconds. Then mix rice with 4 oz. cream cheese and 1/2 cup shredded cheese. Cut premade pizza dough into rectangles, spoon the mixture on top along with chopped cooked chicken and cooked broccoli. Top with another rectangle and pinch to seal the sides closed. Brush with egg wash if you would like. Bake in the oven for 15 minutes at 375° or until golden brown. 
 
Remember to let cool for a few minute because I never had patience as a kid and always burnt the roof of my mouth. Then enjoy one of your favorite childhood treats as a tasty adult meal!

#ad Who else is missing summer weather right about now? We made a little "ice cream" themed food art breakfast featuring @californiaclingpeaches to try to bring on the summer vibes. It's actually peach frozen yogurt bark with some of our other favorite breakfast food!

We love canned California Cling Peaches for so many reasons but one of our favorites is that they are always in season because you can keep them in your pantry all year round! Plus, it's #NationalCannedFoodMonth so we are celebrating all the good things that canned foods offer our family.

Did you know that canned California Cling Peaches have a long shelf life, low cost, and high nutritional value? They also come in 100% recyclable steel food cans! So grab some extra #CaliforniaClingPeaches and usher in summer using my breakfast food art idea!

Directions:
The "ice cream" is actually made with diced California Cling Peaches, yogurt, and mini chocolate chips. Spread everything in a square pan and freeze it for a few hours. Then cut the frozen bark into circle pieces. The cone is a waffle and the flowers are bacon and avocado. To make the bacon flowers, roll a strip of bacon and pin it together with a toothpick. Bake in the oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until cooked all the way through. Breakfast is served!

#ad Who hasn't dreamed of finding a pot of gold at the end of a rainbow? Well, now you can give your friends and family that experience using diced @californiaclingpeaches! We used diced peaches as the gold treasure inside of a chocolate sandwich cookie crust along with a dab of whipped cream and rainbow gummy candy on the top. Directions are below to make this easy magical St. Patrick's Day treat!

We love using California Cling Peaches in recipes for breakfast, lunch, dinner, snacks, and desserts because they are so tasty, versatile, and convenient. Not only that, but they are eco-friendly in 100% recyclable steel food cans, California grown by family farmers, and nutritious. Their cost means more nutrients for less money as well! Simply put, California Cling Peaches check all the boxes for our family. So pick up some extra cans up the next time you are at the store and keep them in your pantry until you need them. 

Peach Pot of Gold Directions: Crush 23-25 chocolate sandwich cookies. Mix together with 5 tbsp. melted butter. Press into greased muffin pan. This should make 6-7 pots of gold. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool. When ready to serve, top with diced California Cling Peaches, a dab of whipped cream, and rainbow candy. Serve immediately.

#ad @CaliforniaClingPeaches are the perfect fruit to make this fun food art owl breakfast! But it doesn't end there because you can create an easy peach crisp (see my previous Reel video for the recipe) for dessert!

Canned California Cling Peaches are known for their value because they are so versatile. This is why it makes so much sense to have a plentiful supply in your pantry. If you want to start with this fun owl breakfast, just use a waffle for the body and spread on cream cheese. Sprinkle on chia seeds. Use California Cling Peaches for the eyes, wings, and feet. Head to your local supermarket to pick up some zesty ¡Yo Quiero!™ dips, along with the other ingredients, and make your family and wallet happy by making these meals.

Breakfast:

Lunch:
Top hot dogs and buns with ¡Yo Quiero!™ Queso, ¡Yo Quiero!™ Bean Dip, ¡Yo Quiero!™ Guacamole, nacho cheese chips, black olives, jalapeños, green onions, red bell pepper, cilantro.

#ad Fall is in full swing which means that parents need after school snack ideas and Halloween ideas. Guess what? @californiaclingpeaches and I are bringing you both! These California Cling Peach Oatmeal cookies with pecans (is it Pee-can or Puh-cahn?) puts a fresh spin on an old classic. Using diced and canned #CaliforniaClingPeaches helps bring a natural sweetness that your kids will love, plus the nutrients and convenience that parents prefer. You will have most, if not all, of the ingredients in your pantry already and you can freeze these cookies to take out for a quick snack when you need it. 

Plus, you can easily give these a Halloween vibe with a little bit of icing, candy googly eyes, or pecans. I've given you a few ideas to start with but I would love to hear how you would decorate these for #SpookySeason! Just remember to stock your pantry with canned California Cling Peaches because they will be ready when you are all season long!

Peach Oatmeal Cookies:
Ingredients: 1 cup diced canned California Cling Peaches, 1/2 cup pecans, 1 cup instant oats, 1 cup flour, 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, 1 1/2 tsp. baking powder, 1/4 tsp. salt, 2 tbsp. melted butter, 1 egg, 1 tsp. vanilla extract, 1/2 cup honey. Optional: halloween icing, candy googly eyes, extra broken pecans for teeth.

Directions: 
1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
2. In bowl mix together oats, flour , pecans, cinnamon, baking powder, and salt.  In separate bowl mix together butter, egg, vanilla extract, and honey. Combine with the dry oat mixture. Mix in the diced peaches.
3. Drop spoonfuls of cookie dough on a greased baking sheet, or use parchment paper. 
4. Bake at 325 degrees for 10-13 minutes. Let cool. Serve, freeze, or decorate for Halloween.

3. Bake according to package directions. Let cool for a few minutes and spread on frosting that came with breadsticks. Drop diced peaches on top. Place peach star at the top. Optionally drop sprinkles on tree.

Dip Recipes:
TOSTITOS® salsa in a football shaped bread bowl:
Ingredients: 1 jar TOSTITOS® salsa, 1 tube of your favorite premade pizza dough, 1 egg, sour cream in a squeezable tube.

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. Roll out pizza dough on cutting board. Cut two strips off of pizza dough. Roll each strip into a tube shape and arrange on top of the other flat pizza dough in the shape of a football. Fold over edges of flat pizza dough and pinch the seams until sealed.
3. Brush beaten egg on top. This will give it a golden brown sheen.
4. Bake in oven for 10-12 minutes or until crust is a golden brown color.
5. Pour TOSTITOS® salsa in middle "bowl" part of football until filled to the top.
6. When ready to serve, squeeze on sour cream in a "football laces" pattern as shown in video.

7 layer dip:
Ingredients: 1 cup of TOSTITOS® queso, 1 cup of TOSTITOS® salsa, 1 can of refried beans, 1 pound cooked ground beef, 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese, 1/2 cup green onions, 2 ounces (1 small can) sliced black olives, Optional: add 1 packet taco seasoning to beef.

Directions:
Layer ingredients in serving bowl. Chill and serve.
